| R4-R7 | Resistor | 499 | 0402 | Daisy Chain Differential Termination |

## 4. Connectivity & Signal Flow
*Internal connectivity follows the BQ79600-Q1 functional requirements.*

**Host Side (Cold Side):**
- **MCU_SPI/UART:** Connects to SCLK, nCS, RX/MOSI, TX/MISO, and nUART/SPI pins.
- **System Control:** NFAULT and INH provide status and wakeup signals to the MCU and Power Supply.

**Isolated Side (Hot Side):**
- **COMH_P/N:** High-side differential pair connected to the next node in the daisy chain via isolation transformer T1.
- **COML_P/N:** Low-side differential pair for ring architecture support, connected via isolation transformer T2.

**Signal Mapping to Ports:**
- **P1.1 (COMHP/N):** BQ79600 COMHP/N -> Isolation T1 -> Connector.
- **P1.2 (COMLP/N):** BQ79600 COMLP/N -> Isolation T2 -> Connector.
- **P2.1 (BAT):** System 12V -> Filtering -> Pin 1 (BAT).
- **P2.2 (VIO):** System 3.3V/5V -> Pin 11 (VIO).
- **P2.4 - P2.7 (SPI):** MCU SPI Bus -> BQ79600 Host Pins (SCLK, nCS, MOSI, MISO).
- **P2.8 (nUART/SPI):** Configuration signal/SPI_RDY -> MCU Pin.
- **P2.9 (NFAULT):** BQ79600 NFAULT -> MCU Interrupt Pin.

- **P2.10 (INH):** BQ79600 INH -> P1.pin6 (to PMIC/LVPS Enable).
- **P2.11 (DVDD):** Internal 1.8V Output -> C12 -> Test Point/Internal use.

## 5. Uncertainties, Assumptions & Confidence
- **Uncertainty:** Final connector selection for the Daisy Chain (P1.1, P1.2) is not defined in the module boundary but inferred as high-voltage rated automotive connectors.
- **Assumption:** SPI interface is the primary host communication protocol (nCS pulled high, nUART/SPI used for mode selection/SPI_RDY).
- **Confidence:** High for core functional blocks and ASIC implementation. Medium for EMC-specific component values (chokes, TVS) which are not explicitly detailed in the baseline schematic segments but are standard for automotive bridge designs.
